+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner is the petition scheduler apparatus. It maintains a kit-static registry of petitioner sources, parses `guild.json` configuration, provides priority dimension types with default-filling, and exposes the `reckoner.petition()` / `reckoner.withdraw()` helper APIs for posting Reckoner-gated writs.
+
+A Reckoner-gated writ is an ordinary Clerk writ in `new` phase that carries `writ.ext['reckoner']` metadata. The Reckoner holds such writs in `new` until a CDC-handler commission decides their fate (approve → `open`, defer → stay `new`, decline → `cancelled`). Spider does not dispatch writs in `new` phase, so gated writs wait safely until the Reckoner acts.
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+```sh
+# In your guild package or kit package
+pnpm add @shardworks/reckoner-apparatus@workspace:*
+```
+
+Requires `@shardworks/clerk-apparatus` (peer dependency via `requires: ['clerk']`).
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+Retrieved via `guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner')`.
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerApi {
+  petition(request: PetitionRequest): Promise<WritDoc>;
+  withdraw(writId: string, reason?: string): Promise<WritDoc>;
+}
+```
+
+### `reckoner.petition(request)`
+
+Post a writ in `new` phase with Reckoner ext set correctly. This is the canonical ergonomic path (Workflow 2 per the contract).
+
+Steps performed internally:
+1. Validates `source` against the petitioner registry (subject to `enforceRegistration` config).
+2. Applies priority defaults for omitted dimensions.
+3. Validates dimension values against the schema.
+4. Calls `clerk.post()` with the writ fields.
+5. Writes `ext.reckoner` via `clerk.setWritExt()`.
+
+Returns the persisted `WritDoc` with `phase: 'new'` and `ext.reckoner` populated.
+
+```typescript
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  // Writ fields (passed to clerk.post)
+  title: 'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body: 'The nexus vision has drifted from the current implementation.',
+  codex: 'nexus',
+  parentId: 'w-...',  // optional
+
+  // Reckoner ext fields
+  source: 'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity: 'serious',
+    scope: 'major-area',
+    time: { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain: ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',       // optional
+  payload: { driftScore: 0.9 }, // optional, opaque to the Reckoner
+  labels: { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' }, // optional
+});
+
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'].source === 'vision-keeper.snapshot'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'].priority.visionRelation === 'vision-violator'
+```
+
+**Priority defaults.** Any omitted priority dimension is filled with the contract default. You can pass a partial `priority` object:
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.petition({
+  title: '...',
+  body: '...',
+  source: 'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: { visionRelation: 'vision-violator' },
+  // severity, scope, time, domain → filled with defaults
+});
+```
+
+**Defaults applied:**
+| Dimension       | Default         |
+|-----------------|-----------------|
+| visionRelation  | `vision-neutral` |
+| severity        | `minor`          |
+| scope           | `minor-area`     |
+| time.decay      | `false`          |
+| time.deadline   | `null`           |
+| domain          | `[]`             |
+
+### `reckoner.withdraw(writId, reason?)`
+
+Withdraw a held writ by transitioning it to `cancelled`. Thin wrapper around `clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: reason })`.
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.withdraw(writ.id, 'Snapshot superseded by newer drift detection.');
+// writ.phase === 'cancelled'
+// writ.resolution === 'Snapshot superseded by newer drift detection.'
+```
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+Under the `reckoner` key in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+| Field                | Type       | Default | Description |
+|----------------------|------------|---------|-------------|
+| `enforceRegistration` | `boolean` | `false` | When `true`, petitions from unregistered sources are declined (writ cancelled). When `false`, a warning is logged and the writ proceeds. |
+| `disabledSources`    | `string[]` | `[]`    | Sources in this list are skipped — the CDC handler leaves their writs in `new` indefinitely. Useful for pausing a source operationally without losing the queued petitions. |
+
+---
+
+## Kit Interface
+
+Petitioner plugins declare their sources via the `petitioners` kit contribution. Add this to your kit's default export:
+
+```typescript
+// my-plugin/src/kit.ts
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source: 'my-plugin.event-name',
+        description: 'Human-readable description of what this source emits.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+};
+```
+
+### `petitioners` schema
+
+```typescript
+interface PetitionerDescriptor {
+  /** Source id in {pluginId}.{kebab-suffix} form. */
+  source: string;
+  /** One-liner describing what situations trigger this source. */
+  description: string;
+}
+```
+
+### Source ID grammar
+
+Source ids follow the form `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`:
+
+- Each segment is kebab-case: lowercase letters, digits, and single hyphens.
+- No leading or trailing hyphens in either segment.
+- Exactly one dot separates the two segments.
+- The `{pluginId}` prefix must match the contributing plugin's derived id.
+
+**Valid examples:**
+- `vision-keeper.snapshot`
+- `patron-bridge.commission`
+- `tech-debt.detected`
+- `clerk.writ-posted`
+
+### Collision policy
+
+Two `petitioners` entries with the same `source` string across any kits are a **hard startup error**. The Reckoner names both contributing plugin ids in the error message. This mirrors the framework-wide collision policy applied to Clerk writ-types, Spider rig-template-mappings, and Fabricator engine designs.
+
+---
+
+## Priority Types
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation: 'vision-blocker' | 'vision-violator' | 'vision-advancer' | 'vision-neutral';
+  severity:       'critical' | 'serious' | 'moderate' | 'minor';
+  scope:          'whole-product' | 'major-area' | 'minor-area';
+  time:           { decay: boolean; deadline: string | null };
+  domain:         Array<DomainTag>;
+};
+
+type DomainTag =
+  | 'security' | 'compliance' | 'cost' | 'feature' | 'quality'
+  | 'infrastructure' | 'documentation' | 'research' | 'ergonomics';
+
+type ComplexityTier = 'mechanical' | 'bounded' | 'exploratory' | 'open-ended';
+```
+
+### Priority helper functions
+
+```typescript
+import {
+  defaultPriority,
+  applyPriorityDefaults,
+  validatePriority,
+} from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+// Returns { visionRelation: 'vision-neutral', severity: 'minor', ... }
+const defaults = defaultPriority();
+
+// Fill omitted fields with defaults
+const full = applyPriorityDefaults({ visionRelation: 'vision-violator' });
+
+// Validate — throws [reckoner]-prefixed error on invalid value
+validatePriority(full);
+```
+
+### `defaultPriority()`
+
+Returns the contract-specified defaults:
+
+```typescript
+{
+  visionRelation: 'vision-neutral',
+  severity:       'minor',
+  scope:          'minor-area',
+  time:           { decay: false, deadline: null },
+  domain:         [],
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## `writ.ext.reckoner` Shape
+
+A writ carrying this ext in `new` phase is a Reckoner-gated writ:
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerExt {
+  source:      string;          // petitioner source id
+  priority:    Priority;        // fully resolved (no partial fields)
+  complexity?: ComplexityTier;  // optional cost estimate
+  payload?:    unknown;         // opaque petitioner data for the rig
+  labels?:     Record<string, string>; // discriminators and tags
+}
+```
+
+The `payload` field is opaque to the Reckoner — it is stored as-is and made available to the rig's engine via standard writ access (`writ.ext['reckoner'].payload`).
+
+---
+
+## Workflow 1 — Direct `clerk.post()`
+
+An apparatus that prefers not to depend on the Reckoner apparatus at runtime can post a Reckoner-gated writ directly via Clerk:
+
+```typescript
+const writ = await clerk.post({ type: 'mandate', title: '...', body: '...' });
+await clerk.setWritExt(writ.id, 'reckoner', {
+  source: 'my-plugin.event',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-neutral',
+    severity: 'minor',
+    scope: 'minor-area',
+    time: { decay: false, deadline: null },
+    domain: [],
+  },
+});
+```
+
+Identical Reckoner behavior to `petition()`. The helper exists for type checking, default handling, and discoverability; it is not a gate.
